Experiment 17
To implement the user if multilevel inheritance 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Aim:

To write a C++ program to implement multilevel inheritance, where one class is derived from another, forming a chain of inheritance.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Algorithm:

1. Start the program.
2. Create a Base class (Class A) with data members and a function.
3. Create a Derived class (Class B) that inherits from Class A.
4. Create another Derived class (Class C) that inherits from Class B.
5. In each class, write functions to access and display its own members.
6. Create an object of the last derived class (Class C).
7. Using the object, call:
Class A function
Class B function
Class C function
8. Display the results.
9. End the program.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source Code (C++):

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

// Base Class
class A {
public:
    void showA() {
        cout << "This is Class A (Base Class)" << endl;
    }
};

// Derived Class from A
class B : public A {
public:
    void showB() {
        cout << "This is Class B (Derived from A)" << endl;
    }
};

// Derived Class from B
class C : public B {
public:
    void showC() {
        cout << "This is Class C (Derived from B)" << endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    C obj;

    cout << "--- Multilevel Inheritance Output ---" << endl;

    obj.showA();  // From Base Class A
    obj.showB();  // From Derived Class B
    obj.showC();  // From Derived Class C

    return 0;
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Output:

--- Multilevel Inheritance Output ---
This is Class A (Base Class)
This is Class B (Derived from A)
This is Class C (Derived from B)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Result:

The program successfully demonstrates multilevel inheritance in C++, where:
Class B inherits from A
Class C inherits from B
Object of class C can access members of A, B, and C


